item.value:
Represents an operation upon two {@code long}-valued operands and producing a {@code long}-valued result. This is the primitive type specialization of {@link BinaryOperator} for {@code long}.

This is a functional interface whose functional method is {@link applyAsLong(long, long)}.

A stage of a possibly asynchronous computation, that performs an action or computes a value when another CompletionStage completes. A stage completes upon termination of its computation, but this may in turn trigger other dependent stages.
